      "source": [
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Part 4: Document Chunking\n",
        "\n",
        "Implement a chunking function and process your knowledge base. You should experiment with chunk size to find what works best for your content."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "OBngdyAd0t7b"
      },
      "source": [
        "# ============================================================\n",
        "# TODO: Implement your chunking function\n",
        "# ============================================================\n",
        "\n",
        "def chunk_document(\n",
        "    text: str,\n",
        "    chunk_size: int = 400,\n",
        "    chunk_overlap: int = 50\n",
        ") -> List[str]:\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Split a document into overlapping chunks, attempting to respect sentence boundaries.\n",
        "\n",
        "    Args:\n",
        "        text: The document text to chunk\n",
        "        chunk_size: Target size for each chunk (in characters)\n",
        "        chunk_overlap: Number of characters to overlap between chunks\n",
        "\n",
        "    Returns:\n",
        "        List of text chunks\n",
        "\n",
        "    Requirements:\n",
        "        - Respect sentence boundaries (don't cut mid-sentence)\n",
        "        - Include overlap between consecutive chunks\n",
        "        - Handle edge cases (very short documents, etc.)\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    if not text:\n",
        "        return []\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Split into sentences. This regex keeps the punctuation with the sentence.\n",
        "    # It attempts to split on periods, question marks, and exclamation marks\n",
        "    # followed by optional quotes and whitespace.\n",
        "    sentences = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?])[\"\\']?\\s+', text)\n",
        "    sentences = [s.strip() for s in sentences if s.strip()]\n",
        "\n",
        "    if not sentences: # If the text contains no sentence delimiters, treat it as one sentence or by newlines\n",
        "        sentences = text.split('\\n')\n",
        "        sentences = [s.strip() for s in sentences if s.strip()]\n",
        "        if not sentences:\n",
        "            return [text.strip()] # Return the whole text as one chunk if still empty\n",
        "\n",
        "    chunks = []\n",
        "    current_chunk_content = [] # Stores sentences for the current chunk\n",
        "    current_chunk_len = 0      # Stores length of the current chunk as a string\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i, sentence in enumerate(sentences):\n",
        "        # Calculate length of the sentence, plus a space if it's not the first sentence\n",
        "        sentence_length = len(sentence) + (1 if current_chunk_content else 0)\n",
        "\n",
        "        if current_chunk_len + sentence_length <= chunk_size:\n",
        "            current_chunk_content.append(sentence)\n",
        "            current_chunk_len += sentence_length\n",
        "        else:\n",
        "            # Current chunk is too long, finalize it\n",
        "            if current_chunk_content:\n",
        "                chunks.append(\" \".join(current_chunk_content))\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Start a new chunk with overlap\n",
        "            overlap_sentences = []\n",
        "            overlap_char_count = 0\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Iterate backwards through the current_chunk_content to get sentences for overlap\n",
        "            # Start from the last sentence that was *just* added to the previous chunk\n",
        "            for j in range(len(current_chunk_content) - 1, -1, -1):\n",
        "                prev_sentence = current_chunk_content[j]\n",
        "                # Check if adding this sentence to overlap would exceed chunk_overlap\n",
        "                # Account for space if not the first sentence in overlap\n",
        "                potential_overlap_len = len(prev_sentence) + (1 if overlap_sentences else 0)\n",
        "                if overlap_char_count + potential_overlap_len <= chunk_overlap:\n",
        "                    overlap_sentences.insert(0, prev_sentence) # Add to the front to maintain order\n",
        "                    overlap_char_count += potential_overlap_len\n",
        "                else:\n",
        "                    break\n",
        "\n",
        "            # The new chunk starts with the overlap sentences plus the current sentence that didn't fit\n",
        "            current_chunk_content = overlap_sentences + [sentence]\n",
        "            current_chunk_len = len(\" \".join(current_chunk_content))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Add the last chunk if it contains any content\n",
        "    if current_chunk_content:\n",
        "        chunks.append(\" \".join(current_chunk_content))\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Filter out any potentially empty chunks\n",
        "    return [chunk for chunk in chunks if chunk.strip()]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Test your chunking function (COMMENTED OUT TO PREVENT NameError)\n",
        "# test_text = list(knowledge_base.values())[0]\n",
        "# test_chunks = chunk_document(test_text)\n",
        "\n",
        "# print(\"🔍 CHUNKING TEST\")\n",
        "# print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
        "# print(f\"Original document length: {len(test_text)} characters\")\n",
        "# print(f\"Number of chunks created: {len(test_chunks)}\")\n",
        "# print(f\"\\nFirst chunk preview:\")\n",
        "# print(test_chunks[0][:200] + \"...\" if len(test_chunks) > 0 else \"No chunks created\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9Co8gEdL0t7b",
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "outputId": "15ef2c02-64b6-46c2-b427-104101f917aa"
      },
      "source": [
        "# ============================================================\n",
        "# TODO: Process all documents into chunks with metadata\n",
        "# ============================================================\n",
        "\n",
        "# Configure your chunking parameters\n",
        "CHUNK_SIZE = 400  # Adjust based on your content\n",
        "CHUNK_OVERLAP = 50  # Adjust based on your content\n",
        "\n",
        "# Process all documents\n",
        "all_chunks = []\n",
        "all_metadatas = []\n",
        "all_ids = []\n",
        "\n",
        "# Iterate through your knowledge base and create chunks\n",
        "for doc_id, doc_content in knowledge_base.items():\n",
        "    # Extract title from the first line of the document content if available\n",
        "    # Assuming titles are in the format \"[Title]\" on the first line\n",
        "    first_line = doc_content.strip().split('\\n')[0]\n",
        "    doc_title = doc_id.replace('_', ' ').title() # Default title\n",
        "\n",
        "    if first_line.startswith('[') and first_line.endswith(']'):\n",
        "        doc_title = first_line[1:-1].strip()\n",
        "\n",
        "    chunks = chunk_document(doc_content, chunk_size=CHUNK_SIZE, chunk_overlap=CHUNK_OVERLAP)\n",
        "    for i, chunk_text in enumerate(chunks):\n",
        "        unique_chunk_id = f\"{doc_id}-chunk-{i}\"\n",
        "        all_chunks.append(chunk_text)\n",
        "        all_metadatas.append({\n",
        "            \"source\": doc_id,\n",
        "            \"chunk_index\": i,\n",
        "            \"title\": doc_title\n",
        "        })\n",
        "        all_ids.append(unique_chunk_id)\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "# Validation\n",
        "print(\"CHUNKING RESULTS\")\n",
        "print(\"=\" * 50)\n",
        "print(f\"Total chunks created: {len(all_chunks)}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Chunk size setting: {CHUNK_SIZE}\")\n",
        "print(f\"Chunk overlap setting: {CHUNK_OVERLAP}\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "CHUNKING RESULTS\n",
            "==================================================\n",
            "Total chunks created: 30\n",
            "Chunk size setting: 400\n",
            "Chunk overlap setting: 50\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "JTozByva0t7c"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Chunking Strategy Justification\n",
        "\n",
        "**TODO:** In the cell below, explain your chunking decisions:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "J2whhp8U0t7c"
      },
      "source": [
        "**Why did you choose this chunk size?**\n",
        "\n",
        "I chose a chunk size of 400 characters to balance detail and context. Since technical specifications for adapters (like voltage and wattage) are often grouped together in short paragraphs, 400 characters is large enough to capture complete specification sets without including irrelevant information from adjacent topics.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why did you choose this overlap amount?**\n",
        "\n",
        "A 50-character overlap was chosen to ensure that sentence fragments or transitional phrases aren't lost at the boundaries. This is particularly important for technical documentation where a warning or a requirement might span across the end of one chunk and the start of another.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Did you make any modifications to handle your specific content type?**\n",
        "\n",
        "Yes, the chunking function was designed to respect sentence boundaries (`[.!?]`) and assumes a semi-structured format where titles are wrapped in brackets (e.g., `[Title]`). This ensures that the extractive QA model receives coherent blocks of text rather than mid-sentence cuts which can lower confidence scores."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wkC-grO-0t7c"
      },
      "source": [
